---
import { siteConfig } from "../../site-config";
import { STEWERSHIP_LEGAL_OPERATOR } from "../../lib/stewardship-legal";

const phone = siteConfig.phoneDisplay?.trim();
const tel = siteConfig.phoneE164?.trim();
const hasPhone = Boolean(phone && tel);
---

<h1>Terms of Service</h1>
<p class="legal-updated"><strong>Last updated:</strong> May 30, 2026</p>

<div class="legal-disclaimer-box">
  <strong>Educational content only</strong>
  Community stewardship pages are provided for <strong>general neighbor education and voluntary
  reference</strong> only. Content — including charts, indexes, and ZIP-local notes — is{" "}
  <strong>illustrative</strong>. It is <strong>not</strong> a licensed contractor estimate,
  engineering report, insurance determination, appraisal, or government bulletin. Confirm conditions
  with qualified professionals before acting on any maintenance decision.
</div>

<h2>1. Acceptance</h2>
<p>By using this website, you agree to these Terms of Service.</p>

<h2>2. What we provide (and do not provide)</h2>
<p>
  {STEWERSHIP_LEGAL_OPERATOR} publishes <strong>non-commercial stewardship briefings</strong> for
  neighbors and volunteers.
</p>
<p>We do <strong>not</strong> provide:</p>
<ul>
  <li>paid dispatch, emergency routing, or on-call contractor assignment</li>
  <li>service scheduling, trip fees, or quote guarantees</li>
  <li>contractor handoffs, lead sales, or marketplace matching from these pages</li>
  <li>insurance, legal, or engineering certifications</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Neighbors who need licensed trade work should engage qualified professionals independently. This
  site does <strong>not</strong> replace on-site inspection or municipal code review.
</p>

<h2>3. Not an emergency services agency</h2>
<p>
  For life-threatening emergencies (fire, gas leak, immediate medical danger), contact{" "}
  <strong>911</strong> or your utility emergency line first.
</p>

<h2>4. Volunteer and fellowship context</h2>
<p>
  References to volunteer desks, neighbor intake, or fellowship outreach describe{" "}
  <strong>informational coordination only</strong>. Participation is voluntary and may depend on
  local availability. No queue depth, arrival time, or outcome is guaranteed.
</p>

<h2>5. Website content</h2>
<p>
  Maps, trend lines, median-style anchors, and educational blocks are planning vocabulary — not
  site-specific measurements, bids, or insurer findings.
</p>

<h2>6. Acceptable use</h2>
<p>
  You agree not to misuse the site, misrepresent affiliation with the fellowship, scrape at scale, or
  attempt to disrupt hosting.
</p>

<h2>7. Disclaimer of warranties</h2>
<p>
  Materials are provided <strong>&ldquo;as is&rdquo;</strong> to the fullest extent permitted by law.
</p>

<h2>8. Limitation of liability</h2>
<p>
  To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect or consequential damages arising
  from use of these educational materials.
</p>

<h2>9. Governing law</h2>
<p>
  These Terms are governed by the laws of the <strong>Commonwealth of Pennsylvania</strong> and
  applicable U.S. federal law, without regard to conflict-of-law rules, except where mandatory
  consumer protections in your state apply.
</p>

<h2>10. Contact</h2>
<p>
  {STEWERSHIP_LEGAL_OPERATOR}
  {hasPhone ? (
    <>
      <br />
      Volunteer reference desk: <a href={`tel:${tel!.replace(/^\+/, "")}`}>{phone}</a>
    </>
  ) : null}
  <br />
  Website: {siteConfig.canonicalOrigin}
</p>
